quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,20,"O you who believe! Obey Allah and His Messenger, and turn not from Him when you hear him speak"
  8,21,"Be not like those who say, \"We hear,\" and yet they hear not"
  8,22,"Verily, the worst of beasts in the sight of Allah are the deaf, the dumb who understand not"
  8,23,"Had Allah known any good in them, He would have made them hear; but had He made them hear, they would have turned away, averse"
  8,24,O you who believe! Respond unto Allah and His Messenger when He calls you to that which quickens you; and know that Allah comes in between a man and his own heart; and that He it is unto Whom you shall be gathered
  8,25,"And fear temptation (or trial, chastisement, oppression, discord, chaos) which falls not exclusively on those of you who have done wrong; but know that Allah is severe in punishment"
  8,26,"Remember when you were few in number and weak in the land, fearing lest people should despoil and snatch you away; then He sheltered you and strengthened you with His aid, and provided you with good things, that per chance (or possibly) you may give thank"
  8,27,"O you who believe! Be not treacherous to Allah and His Messenger; nor knowingly betray your trusts (obligations, duties, responsibilities in respect of wealth, property, confidences, knowledge, talents, time, opportunities, circumstances, power, social po)"
  8,28,"Know that your wealth and your children are but a test, and that with Allah is the highest wage"